     (6)  Do all things necessary to carry out the
functions, powers, and duties set forth in the chapter, which may include
establishment of an advisory committee; and

     (7)  Monitor medical authorizations and waiver
records. [L 1969, c 205, pt of §1; am L 1985, c 15, §3; am L 1992, c 202, §93;
am L 1997, c 88, §4]

